  "text": "In the present study, the standard grain-size scale is used. According to the field classification of fine-grained deposits mud is defined as a sediment containing > 50 volume percentage of clay and silt [CITATION_1] . The sediment denominators were subsequently improved according to details from laboratory analyses. A conventional sieving technique has been used for sandy, non-co- Various parts of channel-fill, except its lowermost and uppermost parts.",
